The paper deals with the impulse response of a microfluidic channel in molecular communication, which involves the transmission of information through the diffusion of molecules. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves solving the diffusion equation, which is a numerical analysis technique (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper deals with the radial distribution of molecules, which is a statistical analysis technique (cs.MS). The application of molecular communication in biomedical engineering is also discussed, which falls under the sub-category of bioinformatics (cs.BI). Finally, the paper deals with the communication performance of the channel, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI).
